üü™ EPIC ‚Äì Return Hardware ‚Äì Equipment Selection, Validation & Cart (Step 1)

Objective

Allow coaches to identify, validate, and add one or multiple equipments to a return process using scan or manual entry, while ensuring ownership consistency, mandatory metadata capture, and explicit confirmation before moving to the next step.

Scope

This epic covers the full Step 1 ‚Äì Select Equipments, including:
	‚Ä¢	Equipment scan / manual entry
	‚Ä¢	Lookup in HAM (MongoDB)
	‚Ä¢	Ownership validation (owner vs depositor)
	‚Ä¢	Equipment details review
	‚Ä¢	Mandatory return metadata
	‚Ä¢	Validation and cart (‚ÄúReturn Summary‚Äù)
	‚Ä¢	Multi-equipment handling
	‚Ä¢	Explicit confirmation before Step 2

‚∏ª

üü¶ US1 ‚Äì Scan or manually enter equipment identifier

User Story

As a coach
I want to scan a barcode or manually enter an equipment identifier
So that I can quickly identify the returned equipment

Description

Display a single input field allowing:
	‚Ä¢	barcode scan
	‚Ä¢	manual typing
	‚Ä¢	accepted identifiers:
	‚Ä¢	barcode
	‚Ä¢	serial number
	‚Ä¢	computer name

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN I am on Step 1 "Select Equipments"
THEN a barcode / identifier input field is visible

AND the field accepts scanned and manually typed values


‚∏ª

üü¶ US2 ‚Äì Automatic search in HAM after 4 characters

User Story

As a coach
I want the system to automatically search HAM once I enter at least 4 characters
So that I can see matching equipments immediately

Description
	‚Ä¢	As soon as the input contains 4 or more characters, a search is triggered in HAM (MongoDB).
	‚Ä¢	Results are displayed in a dropdown list.

Each result shows:
	‚Ä¢	equipment identifier
	‚Ä¢	equipment information (model/type if available)
	‚Ä¢	owner information

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN I enter at least 4 characters
THEN the application searches HAM automatically

AND displays a list of matching equipments with owner information


‚∏ª

üü¶ US3 ‚Äì Handle ‚Äúno match in HAM‚Äù case with manual entry option

User Story

As a coach
I want to be informed when no equipment matches in HAM and be able to enter data manually
So that I can continue the return even if inventory is outdated

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN no result is found in HAM
THEN a message "There is no match in HAM" is displayed
AND a "Fill the form" button is available

WHEN I click "Fill the form"
THEN I am redirected to the manual equipment entry flow


‚∏ª

üü¶ US4 ‚Äì Check owner vs depositor when selecting an equipment

User Story

As a coach
I want the system to check if the equipment owner matches the depositor
So that potential inconsistencies are detected early

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN I select an equipment
THEN the system compares equipment owner with the current depositor

IF they match
THEN the process continues without warning

IF they do not match
THEN a warning modal is displayed


‚∏ª

üü¶ US5 ‚Äì Display owner mismatch warning modal

User Story

As a coach
I want to see a warning modal when the equipment owner differs from the depositor
So that I can confirm or cancel my selection consciously

Description

The modal displays:
	‚Ä¢	Title: Your attention please
	‚Ä¢	Message: ‚ÄúYou selected another owner, please review and confirm it.‚Äù
	‚Ä¢	Two cards:
	‚Ä¢	Depositary (visitor)
	‚Ä¢	Owner selected (from HAM)
	‚Ä¢	Actions:
	‚Ä¢	No, I don‚Äôt ‚Üí cancel selection
	‚Ä¢	Yes, I confirm ‚Üí confirm selection

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN the modal is displayed
AND I click "No, I don't" or close it
THEN I return to the equipment list

WHEN I click "Yes, I confirm"
THEN the selection is confirmed
AND the process continues


‚∏ª

üü¶ US6 ‚Äì Display selected equipment details

User Story

As a coach
I want to see detailed information about the selected equipment and its owner
So that I can verify the correctness before validation

Displayed information (read-only)
	‚Ä¢	Identification:
	‚Ä¢	Barcode / serial number
	‚Ä¢	Computer name
	‚Ä¢	Model
	‚Ä¢	Owner information:
	‚Ä¢	Firstname / lastname
	‚Ä¢	Entity
	‚Ä¢	Function group

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN an equipment is selected
THEN all identification and owner fields are displayed in read-only mode


‚∏ª

üü¶ US7 ‚Äì Mandatory stockroom selection

User Story

As a coach
I want to select the stockroom where the equipment will be stored
So that the physical deposit location is properly tracked

Business Rules
	‚Ä¢	If only one stockroom exists:
	‚Ä¢	it is auto-selected
	‚Ä¢	the field is disabled
	‚Ä¢	If multiple stockrooms exist:
	‚Ä¢	the coach must select one
	‚Ä¢	the field is mandatory

Acceptance Criteria

IF only one stockroom exists
THEN it is auto-selected and disabled

IF multiple stockrooms exist
THEN stockroom selection is mandatory


‚∏ª

üü¶ US8 ‚Äì Mandatory power supply confirmation

User Story

As a coach
I want to specify whether the power supply is returned
So that the return information is complete

Acceptance Criteria

THEN a Yes/No question "Is there a power supply provided?" is displayed
AND answering it is mandatory


‚∏ª

üü¶ US9 ‚Äì Optional comment field

User Story

As a coach
I want to add an optional comment
So that I can provide context about the equipment condition or return circumstances

Acceptance Criteria

THEN a free text comment field is available
AND it is optional


‚∏ª

üü¶ US10 ‚Äì Enable VALIDATE only when mandatory fields are completed

User Story

As a coach
I want the VALIDATE button to be enabled only when all mandatory fields are completed
So that incomplete returns cannot be validated

Rules

Mandatory fields:
	‚Ä¢	stockroom (if applicable)
	‚Ä¢	power supply (Yes/No)

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN mandatory fields are missing
THEN the VALIDATE button is disabled

WHEN all mandatory fields are completed
THEN the VALIDATE button becomes enabled


‚∏ª

üü¶ US11 ‚Äì Add validated equipment to Return Summary (cart)

User Story

As a coach
